<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2007-09-15</DATELINE><TITLE>Optimized synthesis of aminooxy-peptides as glycoprobe precursors for surface-based sugarâ€“protein interaction studies</TITLE><BODY>Abstract An improved procedure for solid phase coupling of Boc-aminooxyacetic acid to peptides is described. By avoiding base-containing activation mixtures which cause over-acylation, it practically suppresses this unwanted side reaction and leads to near quantitative yields of Aoa-peptides, useful as glycoprobe precursors in glycomic studies.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>